  <section id="dataset">
    <h2>Data Context</h2>
    <p>One of the key datasets we analyzed focuses on annual CO₂ emissions by country from 1960 to 2022. This data is sourced from Our World in Data and reflects the long-term impact of industrial activity across regions.</p>
    <p>We found that while some countries have stabilized emissions, global totals continue to rise—especially in rapidly industrializing regions. This reinforces the urgency of coordinated international climate policies.</p>
  </section>

